= PYLADIES =
== Q: Who are you? ==

A: We are [http://blr.pyladies.com Pyladies-Bangalore].


== Q: What is the Pyladies-Dojo all about? ==

A: The dojo is an informal Python-learning session held each week in Bangalore. It was inspired by [http://dojorio.org/about/ DojoRio]
meetups in Brazil where they apply the "[http://smallactsmanifesto.org  small acts manifesto]". The idea being, create a friendly atmosphere which encourages newbies, intermediate and expert programmers to share and learn with the community. 


== Q: Why does this group exist? Are men welcome? ==

A: Our target audience is Women (and those who identify as one) and their friends who have no or limited programming experience. We dont restrict on the basis of gender and our events are welcoming and respectful of trans women and men who want to learn Python. Please RSVP to help the volunteers manage the logistics.


== Q: Are Pyladies events (workshops, meetups, hackathons, sprints) bound by the CoC? ==

A: Yes. The [http://pyfound.blogspot.in/2013/06/announcing-code-of-conduct-for-use-by.html CoC is mandatory] for any event that is funded by grants from the PSF. That said, all the Pyladies dojo events are bound by the [http://www.python.org/psf/codeofconduct/ Python-CoC], in addition to which we expect all attendees to follow our own [http://www.pyladies.com/CodeOfConduct/ Code of Conduct].


== Q: Why is Pyladies having a Python Dojo? ==

A: The short, the code dojos are for women programmers. The long, we are passionate about Python and programming, either use or want to learn Python in a collaborative environment. Our main goal is to share and learn Python, tips and tricks to improve our programming-fu. The focus is on the learning process, as we take small steps towards the solution and try to focus on good development practices. 


== Q: How can I help/volunteer? ==

A: We are always looking for [https://github.com/svaksha/pyladies-dojo/wiki/Volunteers volunteers], space and sponsors for our events. If you wish to host an event in a different part of Bangalore, or in another Indian city, do [pyladies-blr@python.org contact us] for details on how to kickstart this process. 



